9.title: Episode #2.9
9.plot: Hae Sung is finally recognized for her composing talent and the underdogs formulate plan for their performance.

10.title: Episode #2.10
10.plot: Nana's voice takes a turn for the worse and the fate of the idols is thrown into uncertainty. Meanwhile, the lower class is still hard at work.

11.plot: Scandal erupts around JB and Shin Hae Sung just as the idols and students gear up for the "Proposal" mission.

12.title: Episode #2.12
12.plot: JB makes the final proposal for the upcoming duets and Yoo Jin learns about the circumstances behind his being picked as the first Super Idol.

13.plot: When JB is eliminated from the competition, Hae Sung does her best to protect his dreams, but gains insight on his motivations as well.

14.title: Episode #2.14
14.plot: Lee Seul has a special stage in plan for her father and Shin Hae Sung repays JB with one last gift.

15.title: Episode #2.15
15.plot: Hae Sung has to make a decision about a life of composing and the Super Idols prepare for the last audition performance.

16.title: Episode #2.16
16.plot: The final audition comes to an end but what the future holds for the Kirin Art School students is not exactly what you might expect.

1.title: Episode 1
1.plot: Go Hyemi was a student major in classical music but has to give up her dream because of her father's debt by entering Kirin Art High School. However, she needs to get the other two students come along in order for her to enroll the school conditionally. Those two students are Song Samdong, who lives faraway in the country side and Jinguk, the guy whom she accidentally meet while trying to escape from the loan shark. Yoon Baekhee who once was known as Hyemi's tail, however, becoming Hyemi's rival in the school because of those hurting words said by Hyemi. This drama ...

imdb.plot outline: Dream High tells the story of six students at Kirin Art High School who work to achieve their dreams of becoming music stars in the Korean music industry. Go Hye Mi is a student who sings classical music but has to give up her dream by entering Kirin Art High School to pay off her father's debt. However, she needs to get two other students to also come to the school in order for her to enroll in the school conditionally.
